5 "376.1240. 1. For purposes of this section, terms
6 shall have the same meanings as ascribed to them in section
7 376.1350, and the term "self-administered hormonal
8 contraceptive" shall mean a drug that is composed of one or
9 more hormones and that is approved by the Food and Drug
10 Administration to prevent pregnancy, excluding emergency
11 contraception. Nothing in this section shall be construed
12 to apply to medications approved by the Food and Drug
13 Administration to terminate an existing pregnancy.
14 2. (1) Any health benefit plan delivered, issued for
15 delivery, continued, or renewed in this state on or after
16 January 1, 2026, that provides coverage for self-
17 administered hormonal contraceptives shall provide coverage
18 to reimburse a health care provider or dispensing entity for
19 the dispensing of a supply of self-administered hormonal
20 contraceptives intended to last up to ninety days, or
21 intended to last up to one hundred eighty days for generic
22 self-administered hormonal contraceptives. The provisions
23 of this subdivision shall no longer be in effect after
24 December 31, 2026.
